Description 
 
 JOB DETAILS 
 
 Department:  Tracking Operations 
 
 Job Title:  Tracking Operations Specialist 
 
 Reports To (title):  Tracking Operations Lead 
 
 Career Level:  Level 2 
 
 Location:  Global - Remote 
 
 Line Management Responsibility:  none 
 
 Job Purpose: 
 As a Tracking Operations Specialist you are supporting the delivery of the global tracking coverage, being responsible for pre-game planning and supervision of live and post-game operations. Providing direct operational and technical support to all operators during live tracking games. Communicating with clients during live operations. Making sure the post-match production office have received all the tracking and video files from stadium after the games, reporting all the operations incident and software bugs to stakeholders. 
 As a specialist of tracking system manipulation, you participate actively to the quality control of operators and to games coverage, training or customers demonstration. 
 The role can include support of travel booking and stadium access request for tracking operators as well. 
